						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">For example if you use color $20, then with your sequence it will become $20, $20, $00, $00, which is not what you want since you probably wanted sometihng like $20, $10, $00, $0f.</div>
<br />Actually Simon's Quest partially solves this problem by setting palette[x] into
<br />min(origpalette[x], (origpalette[x] &amp; 0x0F) | fadelevel) where fadelevel goes from 0x00 to 0x30 or from 0x30 to 0x00.
<br />This gets $00,$10,$20,$20 instead of $00,$00,$20,$20. For $13, it gets $03,$13,$13,$13. For $34, it gets $04,$14,$24,$34...</div>

